 great dimming is located in the photosphere.\nFurthermore, the long-term spectroscopic and photometric time series suggests\nthat this great dimming does not appear to be a unique phenomenon, but rather\nthat such dimmings do occur more frequently, which motivates further monitoring\nof alpha Ori with facilities such as TIGRE.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 9 Nov 2022 15:31:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-28"}
